Astro-Coord-Precession

A very simple, pure Perl module to precess equatorial coordinates from one epoch
to another, based on the algorithm P. Herget used in the Publications of the
Cincinnati Observatory.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Astro::Coord::Precession

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Astro-Coord-Precession

    CPAN Ratings
        https://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Astro-Coord-Precession

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/Astro-Coord-Precession

    GitHub
        https://github.com/dkechag/Astro-Coord-Precession

